        <body>
            <entry xml:id="entry_ælǧ" xml:lang="os">
                <form xml:id="form_d3219e66" xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>ælǧ</orth></form>
                <form xml:id="form_d3219e69" xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>ælgæ</orth><form xml:id="form_d3219e71" type="variant"><orth>ilǧæ</orth></form></form>
                <sense xml:id="sense_d3219e74"><sense xml:id="sense_d3219e75"><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>отвращение</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>disgust</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense xml:id="sense_d3219e84"><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>гадливость</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>loathing</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense></sense>
                <re xml:id="re_d3219e94">
                    <form xml:id="form_d3219e96" type="lemma"><orth>ælǧ kænyn</orth></form>
                    <sense xml:id="sense_d3219e99"><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>чувствовать отвращение</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>feel loathing</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense>
                </re>
                <re xml:id="re_d3219e110">
                    <form xml:id="form_d3219e112" xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>ælǧag</orth></form>
                    <form xml:id="form_d3219e115" xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>ilǧag</orth></form>
                    <sense xml:id="sense_d3219e118"><sense xml:id="sense_d3219e119"><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                <q>отвратный</q>
                            </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                <q>disgusting</q>
                            </abv:tr></sense><sense xml:id="sense_d3219e128"><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                <q>противный</q>
                            </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                <q>nasty</q>
                            </abv:tr></sense><sense xml:id="sense_d3219e137"><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                <q>мерзкий</q>
                            </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                <q>vile</q>
                            </abv:tr></sense></sense>
                </re>
                <re xml:id="re_d3219e149">
                    <form xml:id="form_d3219e151" type="lemma"><orth>ælǧæd</orth></form>
                    <sense xml:id="sense_d3219e154"><sense xml:id="sense_d3219e155"><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                <q>пресыщение</q>
                            </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                <q>satiation</q>
                            </abv:tr></sense><sense xml:id="sense_d3219e164"><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                <q>отвращение к пище в результате пресыщения</q>
                            </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                <q>disgust for food as a result of satiation</q>
                            </abv:tr></sense></sense>
                </re>
                <re xml:id="re_d3219e175">
                    <form xml:id="form_d3219e177" type="lemma"><orth>mæstælǧædæj fæcær</orth></form>
                    <sense xml:id="sense_d3219e180"><def xml:lang="ru">„живи, пресыщенный горем“ (бранное
                            выражение)</def><def xml:lang="en">"live with grief"
                        (expletive)</def></sense>
                    <note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">. Вероятно, сюда же %iælǵin%i ‘скупой’</note>
                    <note type="comment" xml:lang="en">. Perhaps, ælǵin ‘avid’ concerns here
                        too</note>
                </re>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d3219e195">
                        <quote>zūlk wallonyl ælǧ kodta</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>червяк чувствовал отвращение к дождевому червю</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>the worm was disgusted with the earthworm</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ЮОПам."/><biblScope>III
                            234</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d3219e214" xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>kæd an mægūr, wæddær ilǧæj alkæmæ kæsæn</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>хоть мы и бедны, но мы с брезгливостью смотрим на всех</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>although we are poor, we look at everyone with disgust</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Gurdž._Æduli"/><biblScope>97</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d3219e236" xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>(æci) ǧæwungæj cʼumurdær æma ilǧagdær Ʒæwægiǧæwi n’ adtæj
                            ǧæwungæ</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>грязнее и противнее той улицы не было в Дзауагигау</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>there was no dirtier and nastier street in Dzauagigau</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_MD"/><biblScope>1949 II
                            43</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d3219e258" xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>ilǧag sæ nægæ, sæ xodun</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>отвратителен их шум, их смех</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>their noise, their laughter is disgusting</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Gurdž._Saxi_ræs."/><biblScope>47</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Восходит к <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3219e343" xml:id="mentioned_d3219e283" xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/>
                        <w>*argh-</w></mentioned>; ср. <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3219e348" xml:id="mentioned_d3219e288" xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>ərəɣant-</w>
                        <gloss><q>мерзкий</q></gloss></mentioned> (эпитет, применяемый к преисподней
                    и к вредным насекомым), <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3219e356" xml:id="mentioned_d3219e296" xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>arǧand</w>
                        <gloss><q>алчный</q></gloss></mentioned> (для семантики ср. ос. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ælǧīn"/> ‘скупой’, ‘алчный’), <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3219e366" xml:id="mentioned_d3219e306" xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>*arɣant(ʼrɣʼnt)</w>
                        <gloss><q>гнусный</q></gloss></mentioned>. Рассматриваемый иранский корень
                    имеет все признаки глагольного: ос. %iælǧæd%i ‘пресыщение’ по виду — причастие
                    прош. времени, а ав. %iərəyant-%i- — причастие наст. времени от корня
                    %i*argh-%i. Связь с <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3219e375" xml:id="mentioned_d3219e315" xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>glā-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3219e380" xml:id="mentioned_d3219e320" xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>чувствовать отвращение</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3219e386" xml:id="mentioned_d3219e326" xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>выбиться из сил</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>III 143</biblScope></bibl>)
                    кажется нам мало вероятной ввиду изолированного положения этого древнеиндийского
                            глагола.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Bailey._Asica"/><biblScope>4—5</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">Goes back to <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3219e283" xml:id="mentioned_d3219e343" xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/>
                        <w>*argh-</w></mentioned>; cf. <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3219e288" xml:id="mentioned_d3219e348" xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>ərəɣant-</w>
                        <gloss><q>vile</q></gloss></mentioned> (epithet applied to the underworld
                    and to harmful insects), <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3219e296" xml:id="mentioned_d3219e356" xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>arǧand</w>
                        <gloss><q>avid</q></gloss></mentioned> (for semantics cf. Ossetic <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ælǧīn"/> ‘stingy’, ‘avid’), <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3219e306" xml:id="mentioned_d3219e366" xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>*arɣant(ʼrɣʼnt)</w>
                        <gloss><q>abominable</q></gloss></mentioned>. The Iranian root in question
                    has all the features of a verbal one: Ossetic %iælǧæd%i ‘satiation’ is a past
                    participle in form, and in Avestian %iərəyant-%i- is a present participle from
                    the stem %i*argh-%i. Relation to <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3219e315" xml:id="mentioned_d3219e375" xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>glā-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3219e320" xml:id="mentioned_d3219e380" xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>feel disgust</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3219e326" xml:id="mentioned_d3219e386" xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>feel exhausted</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>III 143</biblScope></bibl>)
                    seem implausible due to the isolated position of this ancient Indian
                            verb.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Bailey._Asica"/><biblScope>4—5</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
            </entry>
